Tweet text: #TechTuesday - new #dataset for those who work with #SeaIce! ATLAS/ICESat-2 L3B Daily and Monthly Gridded Sea Ice Freeboard is now available from @NSIDC.  More information on the dataset webpage: https://t.co/wzd7XT9kxQ

#SharingSciFri: did you miss @IASC_Arctic's #ASSW2020? Have no fear, the #Arctic Science Summit Week Summary report is now available! Read about the the business meetings, the science presentations, and the Arctic Observing Summit. Download it here: https://t.co/q4ySnvf2jc

#WarmingWednesday: what role are #aersols playing in the #Arctic? A new Perspective from @NatureClimate makes the case for more observation and modelling work on aerosol-climate interactions. Read more: https://t.co/xMvJB31JnG https://t.co/S18Fh3G0mU

We've found #microplastics in almost everywhere from the surface to the ocean's depths. It's no surprise, then, that microplastics are in the remotest places in the #Arctic. In every 100 g of sediment, 0.33 anthropogenic particles were found. Read more: https://t.co/ThqZoMf0QS https://t.co/MBFZgWT2No

#Arctic researchers, do you need data about the #Antarctic? Quantarctica is a collection of Antarctic geographical datasets for research, education, operations, and management that works on QGIS. Check out this great #OpenSource resource! #TechTuesday https://t.co/fiEGGDxNIN
Deadline for the first review of the Community Engagement and Outreach Coordinator position is tomorrow. Come join our team! #scicommjobs https://t.co/V9G6piaEtR

Cross-cutting research: a #NewPaper out from @PerttiScience et al uses methods from a caribou dataset in the @arcticdatactr to help them study #Arctic snow isotope hydrology. Paper here: https://t.co/YN7TIwx7h3 Dataset here: https://t.co/PEjOHCsphI https://t.co/iQM40w4HJx

#TechTuesday: new #data available! Researchers can now access updated products - #Greenland weather stations, #ice discharge, ice velocity, freshwater runoff, and more - available from the @PromiceGL data portal. https://t.co/8ikajs4vBg https://t.co/hS0Ng4fiOO

How do #wildfires affect the density & diversity of trees & understory communities in #Siberian #Arctic forests? Read this #NewPaper to discover cascading impacts that increased wildlife activity can have on forest structure: https://t.co/p6nQgCZfG0 Data: https://t.co/0e89rKBcUd
